Title: Rayleigh-Schr\"{o}dinger Perturbation Theory Based on Gaussian

Wavefunctional ApprochAuthors: Wen-Fa Lu, Chul Koo Kim, Jae Hyung Yee and Kyun Nahm

Comments: revtex, 7 pages, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D64 (2001) 025006; Erratum-ibid. D66 (2002) 069901

A Rayleigh-Schr\"{o}dinger perturbation theory based on the Gaussianwavefunctional is constructed. The method can be used for calculating theenergies of both the vacuum and the excited states. A model calculation iscarried out for the vacuum state of the $\lambda\phi^4$ field theory.